# compiler/v5_6.cyml ─ 11 entries
# v5_6_x_optimization_arc_gotchas_bundle           — IR-pass debugging methodology + ESETCC + parse_ctrl + IR_RAX_CLOBBER + const-fold + NOP-fill
# v5_6_18_to_26_regalloc_arc_gotchas_bundle        — regalloc default-on, Phase O4 split, ECALLPOPS r12-r14 clobber, picker bisection, EPOPARG cancel
# stdlib_alloc_grow_step_vs_requested_size         — Bump-allocator grow must cover requested size, not a fixed delta
# sit_symptom_2_was_sankoch_encoder_not_cyrius     — sit's "fsck unreadable objects" was a sankoch deflate bug, not a cyrius alloc bug
# two_consecutive_platform_drift_pins_were_both_fn_main_fixture_bugs — v5.6.33 Mach-O + v5.6.36 PE: same fn-main fixture bug, not regressions
# libssl_needs_fdlopen_not_dynlib_open             — libssl recursive pthread mutex __kind lives in glibc TCB; zeroed TCB deadlocks
# version_string_must_not_be_hardcoded_in_source   — Route --version through src/version_str.cyr; never hardcode in source
# stdlib_tls_hook_surface_via_fn_pointer_not_callback_registry — One hook fnptr + one symbol-resolver = bounded surface; consumers compose
# sysv_odd_stack_args_rsp_alignment_violation      — SysV requires rsp 16-aligned at every CALL; ECALLPOPS for n>6 left it 8-aligned for odd nextra
# pp_ifdef_pass_helpers_must_take_src_base         — Same class as v5.6.30: PP helpers must thread src_base for source > 524288 B
# heap_cap_growth_pattern_compiler_grows_to_fit_language — Grow the cap, don't trim the stdlib/test/language; reshuffle methodology

# compiler/v5_7.cyml ─ 15 entries
# ts_lex_jsx_lookahead_is_arrow_jsx_terminators    — TS_LOOKAHEAD_IS_ARROW must treat JSX closing tokens as scope terminators
# ts_lex_jsx_disambig_byteskip_only                — Pre-flight BYTE_SKIP balance check is sufficient JSX-vs-generic-arrow disambiguation
# ts_lex_jsx_mode_stack_design                     — JSX lex modes 4=JSX_TAG / 5=JSX_TEXT / 8=JSX_EXPR on the template stack
# cx_drift_silent_accumulation_lesson              — main_cx.cyr accumulated 4+ silent drift breakages; v5.7.11 fix + CI gate
# target_cx_backend_marker_path_b                  — _TARGET_CX backend marker for path-B guards on direct x86-byte emits
# heap_reshuffle_pattern_v5_7_10                   — input_buf 512KB → 1MB via +0x100000 shift of 95 distinct heap-region addresses
# forked_helper_offset_typo_cx_backend_v5_7_23     — cx codegen literal-arg propagation bug — TOKVAL read from wrong heap region
# verify_slot_premise_aarch64_f64_stubs_v5_7_30    — aarch64 f64 stubs returned 0 for years; surfaced via premise verification on a polyfill task
# audit_silent_skip_is_false_green_v5_7_36         — scripts/check.sh's silent-skip on missing fmt/lint reported false-PASS
# distlib_per_module_read_cap_v5_7_36              — distlib per-module read buffer was 65535 B; modules > 64 KB silently truncated
# auto_deps_gate_inflates_self_host_size_v5_7_38   — Adding `cyrius soak` to auto-deps gate blew the 2MB expanded-source cap
# lsp_globals_before_fn_definitions_v5_7_39        — Top-level `var X` must be declared before any fn body that references X
# distlib_64kb_truncation_v5736                    — pre-5.7.36 distlib silently truncated source files >64KB; mabda's backend_native.cyr surfaced it
# lint_fmt_per_file_in_5_7                         — cyrius lint / fmt --check became per-file in 5.7.x; bare repo-wide form is gone
# fn_keyword_in_param_position                     — `fn` is reserved; parser surfaces the error at the NEXT fn definition, not the offending one

